<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="480" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,977,1578]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,977,1002]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group VIII key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier" box="[643,848,977,1002]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1966) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part III. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Megaselia. Studia Entomologica, 8, 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1966">
Borgmeier (
<number box="[780,840,977,1002]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[862,1028,978,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wiegmanae">
<emphasis box="[862,1028,978,1001]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. wiegmanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fails the key at couplet 
<number box="[1307,1334,978,1002]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" value="11.0">11</number>
where it lacks either the enlarged genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" box="[572,851,1013,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globipyga">
<emphasis box="[572,724,1013,1037]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. globipyga</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
or the large hypandrium of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wood." authorityName="Wood." box="[1173,1437,1013,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicostalis">
<emphasis box="[1173,1354,1013,1037]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. brevicostalis</emphasis>
Wood.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[151,317,1050,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wiegmanae">
<emphasis box="[151,317,1050,1073]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. wiegmanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, like 
<taxonomicName box="[383,564,1049,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicostalis">
<emphasis box="[383,564,1049,1073]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. brevicostalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is part of the 
<taxonomicName box="[734,891,1050,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtineura">
<emphasis box="[734,891,1050,1073]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. curtineura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of 
<taxonomicName box="[1037,1153,1049,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1037,1153,1049,1073]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">Megaselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the two species are similar. In addition to the aforementioned large hypandrium of 
<taxonomicName box="[897,1081,1085,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicostalis">
<emphasis box="[897,1081,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. brevicostalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1268,1086,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wiegmanae">
<emphasis box="[1099,1268,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. wiegmanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a slightly longer costal index (0.42–0.44 compared to 0.40–0.43), and only 
<number box="[885,899,1122,1146]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
alular setae (
<quantity box="[1049,1092,1121,1146]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1278,1121,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicostalis">
<emphasis box="[1099,1278,1121,1145]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. brevicostalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1303,1387,1121,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 87 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,255,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[150,1436,241,1829]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 87 – 92. Male genitalia, left lateral. 87. Megaselia rodriguezorum. 88. Megaselia sacatelensis. 89. Megaselia seaverorum. 90. Megaselia sidneyae. 91. Megaselia steptoeae. 92. Megaselia wiegmanae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242988/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">
Fig. 
<number box="[1355,1387,1122,1146]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" value="92.0">92</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
